				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Having fun with my BoH....<a name="10862"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 28 03 11:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I map songs to F keys (that doesn't matter tho, although I would be happy to argue the significant benefit of this).
<br />

<br />
I have my primary/secondary hotkeyed for instrument and weapon swaps (an open bag sits righ next to the hotkey bank).
<br />

<br />
When I want to twist in the BoH, I just leave the mouse cursor over it and:
<br />

<br />
f1/rightclick/f1
<br />
f2/f2
<br />
f3/rightclick/f3
<br />
f4/f4
<br />

<br />
Thats if I feal the Niv's is really important at the time, which is usually  the only time I use BoH. That ads about .2 of a sec to the f1 and f3 twists...not a bad tradeoff, If you are twisting 4 atm (I am happy to argue the validity of four twists in certain situations).
<br />

<br />
Otherwise, in a three twist, you just need to add it once.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
