		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Having fun with my BoH....<a name="10865"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 28 03 10:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For BoH, I use the Nostromo N50 (http://www.tuplay.com/display.asp?i=69&amp;p=1) for my twists, and it's well worth the $20 bucks.
<br />

<br />
My hot keys are the standard single-key macros (/stopsong, /cast#) programmed so I have to hit 1,2,3,4 to twist.  I then programmed the side &quot;thumb-paddle UP&quot; button to macro &quot;enter, type: stopsong&quot; to stop whatever is playing in my twist.  Finally, in the fifth slot on my hotkeys.
<br />

<br />
The sequence of the twist is 1,2,3,4, thumbpad up, 5, 1,2,3,4, thumbpad up,5, etc.  I like the setup because I can get a 5 song twist relatively easily and it frees up my mouse for mouse-look, movement, or whatever else comes to mind (eating sammich).
<br />

<br />
I can keep all 5 songs up most of the time, though any lag or missed note causes a drop.  Still, its consistent enough to make it worth the extra effort.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
